<article>
  <title></title>

  <section>
    <title>Roadmap</title>

    <para>Done:</para>

    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
        <para>Support W3C DOM model for all existing elements. (done)</para>
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
        <para>Make sure the most important checkstlye issues are addressed,
        such as full JavaDoc documentation. (done)</para>
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
        <para>Refactor to provide a more future-compatible API (done)</para>
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
        <para>Modify layout code to use "float" instead of "int" coordinates
        (done)</para>
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
        <para>support content markup (done)</para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>

    <para>Future ideas (currently there is no active work on these going
    on):</para>

    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
        <para>use axsl-font-r for automatic font selection (delayed
        indefinetly)</para>
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
        <para>provide support for CSS, maybe through <ulink
        url="http://xmlgraphics.apache.org/batik">batik-css</ulink>.</para>
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
        <para>support <ulink url="http://www.w3.org/TR/MathML3">MathML
        3</ulink>.</para>
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
        <para>Implement a linebreaking algorithm</para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>

    <para>General issues:</para>

    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
        <para>Address the Issues from the <ulink
        url="./issue-tracking.html">issue tracking system</ulink>.</para>
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
        <para>Resolve the <ulink url="./taglist.html">TODO items</ulink> from
        the code.</para>
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
        <para>Clean up <ulink url="./checkstyle.html">Checkstlye</ulink>
        issues.</para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
  </section>
</article>
